By Martins Ifijeh Nigeria has recorded 131 new cases of COVID-19, bringing to 56,735 the number of confirmed cases in the country. Announcing this yesterday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) said Lagos recorded 45 new cases; Kaduna and Plateau, 17 each; Federal Capital Territory (FCT),16; Delta and Niger, six each; Kwara, five; Oyo, three; Akwa Ibom, Ekiti, Cross River, Enugu, Osun and Sokoto, two each; while Bauchi, Ebonyi, Katsina and Rivers recorded one each. It said: “Nigeria has so far recorded 56,735 confirmed cases of COVID-19. 48,092 patients have been discharged, while 1,093 persons have died.”